<docbook><section><title>OplmgrHTTPODBCAdministratorStats</title><para> </para><title> OpenLink License Manager Usage Notes -- HTTP-based ODBC Administrator License Statistics </title> OpenLink License Manager Usage Notes -- HTTP-based ODBC Administrator License Statistics 
<para>The HTTP-based ODBC Administrator shipped with the Single-Tier product for Unix-like OS provides a License Statistics page to enable the details of the license in use on a given machine to be viewed.</para><para>To view this page, ensure the  HTTP-based ODBC Administrator is started -- </para><programlisting>sh iodbc-admin-httpd.sh start
</programlisting><para> Then load the HTTP-based ODBC Administrator in a web browser -- </para><programlisting>http://{admin-hostname}:{portno}/
</programlisting><para>-- e.g.
 -- </para><programlisting>http://localhost:8000/
</programlisting><para>-- and drill down to <emphasis>Client Components Administration</emphasis> -&gt; <emphasis>View <ulink url="OpenLink">OpenLink</ulink> Client License Information</emphasis> in the left frame --<figure><graphic fileref="OplmgrHTTPODBCAdministratorStats/adminlicdetails.png" /></figure></para>
<para>Click on the <emphasis>details</emphasis> linkto see more detailed information about a specific license: <figure><graphic fileref="OplmgrHTTPODBCAdministratorStats/stlicdetails.png" /></figure></para><para>Note these pages display the number of logical processors (CPUs) the License Manager has detected on the host it is running on.</para><para> </para></section></docbook>